        "can_see_hidden_post": false,
        "can_unaccept_answer": false,
        "can_view_edit_history": true,
        "can_wiki": false,
        "cooked": "<p>Its slow not because the geometry is complex, but because BOSL2 features are expensive.<br>\nUse BOSL only where it actually adds value and go bare metal OpenSCAD elsewhere.<br>\nAvoid global fn, it massively hurts performance on small parts.<br>\nInstead, assign fn per part and derive it from a target resolution.<br>\nIf using difference with more than two operands, wrap the union in render to reduce CSG overhead.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">resolution = 0.2;\nfunction fn(r,d) = floor(2*(r?r:d?d/2:1)*PI/resolution);\nmodule fncircle(r=undef, d=undef, resolution=resolution) {\n  radius = (r!=undef)?r:(d!=undef)?d/2:1;\n  facets = floor(2*radius*PI/resolution);\n  circle(r=radius,$fn=facets);\n}\n// circle(d=5,$fn=fn(d=5));\n// fncircle(d=5);\n// fncircle(d=5,resolution=1);\n</code></pre>",
        "created_at": "2025-12-14T22:07:15.082Z",
        "current_user_reaction": null,
        "current_user_used_main_reaction": false,
        "deleted_at": null,
        "display_username": "Professional3 D",
        "edit_reason": null,
        "flair_bg_color": null,
